<issue num="336" status="CD1">
<title>Clause 17 lack of references to deprecated headers</title>
<section><sref ref="[library]"/></section>
<submitter>Detlef Vollmann</submitter>
<date>05 Sep 2001</date>

<discussion>
<p>From c++std-edit-873:</p>

<p><sref ref="[headers]"/>, Table 11.  In this table, the header
&lt;strstream&gt; is missing.</p>

<p>This shows a general problem: The whole clause 17 refers quite
often to clauses 18 through 27, but D.7 is also a part of the standard
library (though a deprecated one).</p>

</discussion>

<resolution>

<p>To <sref ref="[headers]"/> Table 11, C++ Library Headers, add
"&lt;strstream&gt;".</p>

<p>In the following places, change "clauses 17 through 27" to "clauses
17 through 27 and Annex D":</p>

<ul>
<li><sref ref="[intro.refs]"/> Normative references/1/footnote 1</li>
<li><sref ref="[intro.defs]"/> Definitions/1</li>
<li><sref ref="[dcl.dcl]"/> Library introduction/9</li>
<li><sref ref="[description]"/> Method of description (Informative)/1</li>
<li><sref ref="[character.seq]"/> Character sequences/1/bullet 2</li>
<li><sref ref="[functions.within.classes]"/> Functions within classes/1</li>
<li><sref ref="[objects.within.classes]"/> Private members/1/(2 places)</li>
<li><sref ref="[requirements]"/> Library-wide requirements/1</li>
<li><sref ref="[headers]"/> Headers/4</li>
<li><sref ref="[replacement.functions]"/> Replacement functions/1</li>
<li><sref ref="[global.functions]"/> Global or non-member functions/2</li>
<li><sref ref="[protection.within.classes]"/> Protection within classes/1</li>
</ul>


</resolution>

</issue>
